\section*{Problem}

Find the radius of a circular orbit of an electron with energy \SI{5}{\kilo\electronvolt} in a magnetic field of \SI{10^{-2}}{\tesla}. [Osmania University 1992]

\section*{Solution}

The radius of the circular orbit of a charged particle in a magnetic field is given by the formula:
\[
r = \frac{mv}{qB}
\]
where:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \( m \) is the mass of the electron (\( m = 9.11 \times 10^{-31} \, \mathrm{kg} \)),
    \item \( v \) is the velocity of the electron,
