    \item \( B \) is the magnetic field (\( B = \SI{10^{-2}}{\tesla} \)).
\end{itemize}

The kinetic energy of the electron is given by:
\[
E = \frac{1}{2}mv^2
\]
Solving for \( v \), we have:
\[
v = \sqrt{\frac{2E}{m}}
\]

Given \( E = \SI{5}{\kilo\electronvolt} = 5 \times 10^3 \times 1.6 \times 10^{-19} \, \mathrm{J} \), we can substitute this into the equation for \( v \):
\[
v = \sqrt{\frac{2 \times 5 \times 10^3 \times 1.6 \times 10^{-19}}{9.11 \times 10^{-31}}}
\]

Substituting \( v \) back into the formula for \( r \):
\[
r = \frac{m \sqrt{\frac{2E}{m}}}{qB} = \frac{\sqrt{2mE}}{qB}
\]

Now, substituting the known values:
\[
r = \frac{\sqrt{2 \times 9.11 \times 10^{-31} \times 5 \times 10^3 \times 1.6 \times 10^{-19}}}{1.6 \times 10^{-19} \times 10^{-2}}
\]

Calculating the above expression gives the radius \( r \).

