\section*{Ampère's Law and Magnetic Field Calculation}

\subsection*{Ampère's Law}

Ampère's Law relates the tangential component of the magnetic field $\vb{B}$ summed around a closed curve $C$ to the current $I_c$ passing through the area enclosed by the curve. Mathematically, it is expressed as:

\begin{equation}
    \oint_C \vb{B} \cdot \dd{\vb{l}} = \mu_0 I_c
\end{equation}

